'''Okuma Kabuto Festival''' (お熊甲祭) is the annual [[Reisai|regular festival]] of {{ill|Kumakabuto Arakashi Hiko Shrine|ja|久麻加夫都阿良加志比古神社}}, located in {{ill|Nanao|ja|七尾市}}, {{ill|Ishikawa Prefecture|ja|石川県}}, in the {{ill|Nakajima, Ishikawa|lt=Nakajima|ja|中島町 (石川県)}} district of Miyamae. Held every year on {{ill|September 20|ja|9月20日}}, it is also referred to as the '''Hatsuka Festival''' (二十日祭, Hatsuka Matsuri or Hatsuka Sai).<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Okuma Kabuto Festival: A Nationally Designated Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property|url=https://www.city.nanao.lg.jp/koryu-s/event/9gatsu/okumakabuto-.html|website=Nanao City|access-date=2022-10-15|language=ja}}</ref> It is one of the {{ill|Four Major Festivals of Nanao|ja|七尾四大祭}} along with the {{ill|Seihakusai|ja|青柏祭}}, {{ill|Mukōda Fire Festival|ja|向田の火祭り}}, and {{ill|Ishizaki Hōtō Festival|ja|石崎奉燈祭}}.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.city.nanao.lg.jp/kikaku-s/shise/sesaku/1sogokekaku/honpen/documents/kihonkeikaku_1_4_5.pdf|title=Basic Plan: Chapter 1, Arts and Culture|access-date=2024-08-04|publisher=Nanao City|page=88}}</ref>{{Refnest|group="Note"|text=The Seihakusai, Ishizaki Hōtō Festival, {{ill|Nanao Gion Festival|ja|七尾祇園祭}}, and {{ill|Nanao Port Festival|ja|七尾港まつり}} are sometimes listed as the four major festivals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yamaguchi-ev.com/ishikawa-event/1692/|title=Events in Ishikawa Prefecture in May|access-date=2024-08-04|publisher=Yamaguchi Corporation}}</ref>}}
Due to its unique use of massive framed banners (''waku-hata'') measuring up to 20 meters, the festival is designated as the '''Framed Banner Procession of the Kumakabuto Hatsuka Festival''' (熊甲二十日祭の枠旗行事), a [[Nationally Designated Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property]] since 1981.<ref name="database">{{国指定文化財等データベース2|name=Framed Banner Procession of the Kumakabuto Hatsuka Festival|register=302|item=61|year=1981|jyear=昭和56|month=1|date=21|cat1=Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property}}</ref><ref name=":0" />
